    <!-- Main Content -->
    <section id="overview">
        <div class="content-container">
            <h2>Project Overview</h2>
            <p>
                Jenkins Remoting is a Java-based library that enables the communication between Jenkins controllers and agents. 
                It provides a protocol for transferring data, managing job execution, and handling remote access for distributed builds.
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Efficient Communication:</strong> Optimized for low-latency, high-throughput communication.</li>
                <li><strong>Secure Data Transfer:</strong> Utilizes secure channels to ensure data integrity.</li>
                <li><strong>Cross-Platform Support:</strong> Compatible with various platforms like Linux, Windows, and macOS.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="documentation">
        <div class="content-container">
            <h2>Documentation</h2>
            <p>For detailed information about the Jenkins Remoting project, please visit the official documentation:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="https://www.jenkins.io/project/jenkins-remoting/" target="_blank">Jenkins Remoting Official Documentation</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://github.com/jenkinsci/remoting" target="_blank">GitHub Repository</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://www.jenkins.io/doc/" target="_blank">Jenkins Documentation</a></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="installation">
        <div class="content-container">
            <h2>Installation Guide</h2>
            <p>Follow the instructions below to install Jenkins Remoting on your machine:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Ensure you have a running Jenkins instance (either controller or agent).</li>
                <li>Download the latest remoting.jar from the Jenkins remoting GitHub releases page.</li>
                <li>Run the following command to start the remoting agent:</li>
                <pre>java -jar remoting.jar -jnlpUrl <your-jenkins-master-url>/computer/<agent-name>/slave-agent.jnlp</pre>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="contribute">
        <div class="content-container">
            <h2>Contribute to Jenkins Remoting</h2>
            <p>The Jenkins Remoting project is open-source, and we welcome contributions. You can help by:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Reporting bugs or suggesting new features</li>
                <li>Submitting pull requests on the GitHub repository</li>
                <li>Joining the Jenkins community to discuss and collaborate on future development</li>
            </ul>
            <p>For more information on contributing, please visit the <a href="https://github.com/jenkinsci/remoting" target="_blank">GitHub Repository</a>.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

